  "text": "The three components are somewhat independent, but not completely so. In particular, [CITATION_1] fixed the segmentation algorithm to be BestLink, and used a latent structural SVM to learn the classifier in order to minimize errors in the final segmentation. They found that this yielded slightly better results (3% gain in precision, 2% gain in recall) compared to learning the classifier over pairs of observations (the \"AdaptClu\" algorithm in [CITATION_2] ).",
